    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1979-06-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1979-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="262"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <head>262. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">Brzezinski</persName>) to Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> and Secretary of Defense
                        <persName corresp="#p_BH_2">Brown</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d262fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Staff Material, Middle East, Subject File, Box 11, Egypt:
                        6/79. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1979-06-12">June 12, 1979</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Military Assistance for Egypt (S)</item>
                </list>
                <p>In the light of yesterday’s discussions with Vice President <persName
                        corresp="#p_MH_1">Mubarak</persName>,<note n="2" xml:id="d262fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d260">Document 260</ref>.</note> it would be useful to have a
                    prompt review<note n="3" xml:id="d262fn3">See <ref target="#d274">Document
                            274</ref>.</note> of the practicalities <pb facs="0901" n="866"
                        xml:id="pg_866"/> of enhanced <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> military
                    assistance to Egypt, perhaps stretched out over a somewhat longer period of
                    time. The President would like to have the above by the time of his return from
                        Vienna.<note n="4" xml:id="d262fn4">See <ref target="#d260fn7">footnote 7,
                            Document 260</ref>.</note> (S)</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Zbigniew Brzezinski</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
